HEADWORD: Formalism
<hw>Form"al*ism</hw> <pr>(f⟦ocir⟧rm"⟦ait⟧l*⟦icr⟧z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>The practice or the doctrine of strict adherence to, or dependence
on, external forms, esp. in matters of religion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

